File: Cabinet says the latest interventions are in line with studies on the country’s demand and supply. CAPE TOWN - Cabinet has given the go-ahead to release government’s latest energy blueprint. This as the economy takes another knock from the latest round of load-shedding. The plan proposes nine interventions to ensure the country responds to its energy demands until 2030. READ: Government working on reducing electricity cost: Mantashe Pressure has been mounting on mineral resources minister Gwede Mantashe to unveil the Integrated Resource Plan. The draft IRP was released more than a year ago for public comment. Cabinet says the latest interventions are in line with studies on the country’s demand and supply. READ: The basics of the IRP policy It says the plan pursues a diversified energy mix and reduces reliance on a single or a few primary energy sources. Mantashe is expected to release the plan on Friday.